	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				This is directed to all you smiths who think 10pp per AC is a good idea. I believe this started as an extension of the banded thing, and it doesn't really make much sense there either, but you can trivialize sooner there and it costs less anyway.<BR>
I'll give two separate arguments for why any amount of pp per AC doesn't make sense.<BR>
Argument 1 (you get what you pay for):<BR>
My first argument is that 10AC means a lot more on say a visor than it does on a chestplate. e.g. there aren't many good comparisons because stats muddy this too much. But to get Arms slot armor at 20ac or greater you need to be about level 45 or more whereas you can get a breastplate at around 20 (not counting purchasing making it). The same holds true for the other slots. A 20 AC bracer is amazing, a 20 AC breastplate is ho-hum.<BR>
<BR>
Argument 2 (markup on materials):<BR>
The best example here is FS Breastplate vs. FS Greaves. They both require exactly the same components except for the mold. BP mold costs about 21pp and leg mod costs 19pp if we say the other materials cost around 75pp then that's 96 for the bp and 94 for the legs. Yet at 10pp per AC the BP sells for 190pp and the legs for 120pp. Now it may be possible to make money on this when your skill gets to 200+. The supply cost is exactly the same. The demand is the same. Hence economics should dictate that they cost about the same. Do you think you could convince your auto-dealer to sell cars at $100 per horsepower, or CompUSA to sell computers at $3 per MHz i think not. I'm not saying we should rip our customers off. My prices are 2x base materials. And this works out to around 10pp per ac ON AVERAGE. Yes, the leggings are more expensive, but for instance the bracers are much cheaper. They cost 32pp to m ake and i sell for 65pp rather than 90pp as the AC cost would dictate. Overall my price for a full suit is within 20pp of the full suit price at 10pp/ac. <BR>
<BR>
The 1pp/ac rule is nice for banded cause it's simple, and it's not worth haggling over 1 or 2 platinum. But it shouldn't extend to FS armor. When people ask me to make them plate at 10pp per AC I just won't make them leggings or other pieces that fall into that category. Eventually they pick them up used or come back to me, or bankrupt some other poor smith. Some of them don't have tradeskills so they don't think about the cost of failures. I sold armor to one guy lately who wanted leggings for 120pp. I explained to him that they cost almost 100pp just to make. And his response was &quot;that's 20pp in your pocket.&quot;<BR>
I'm not trying to get rich with smithing. If I wanted to make money I'd do better killing Hill Giants. Even if my smithing skill was 220+ and all FS plate was trivial there are still faster ways to make money. But I don't want to be losing money when I make armor for people. We already spent between 500 and 1000pp getting our skills up to where we can make plate armor. Is it to much to ask that we make a little of that back?
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
